.TH "comedi_buf_read_samples" 9 "comedi_buf_read_samples" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
comedi_buf_read_samples \- Read sample data from COMEDI buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned int" comedi_buf_read_samples
.BI "(struct comedi_subdevice *s "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nsamples "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "s" 12
COMEDI subdevice.
.IP "data" 12
Pointer to destination.
.IP "nsamples" 12
Maximum number of samples to read.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Read up to \fInsamples\fP samples from the COMEDI acquisition data buffer
associated with the subdevice, mark it as read and update the acquisition
scan progress.  Limit the number of samples read to the number available.
Set the COMEDI_CB_BLOCK event flag if any samples are read to cause waiting
tasks to be woken when the event flags are processed.
.SH "RETURN"
The amount of data read in bytes.
